          <h2>News</h2>
          <br />
          
<span style="font-weight: bold;">7 November 2017</span><br />
          There are currently several fully-funded PhD positions open to work in my group, and a few to work on projects I collaborate with (i.e. with me as second supervisor).
<ul>
<li style="margin-left: 40px;"> Microscopy in scattering media (in collaboration with <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/physics-astronomy/staff/cs463">Prof. Christian Soeller</a>): <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/studying/funding/award/?id=2842">link</a>.</li>
<li style="margin-left: 40px;"> Random walks in inhomogeneous media and their applications in Mesoscopic Physics and Evolutionary Dynamics (in collaboration with <a href="https://www.exeter.ac.uk/livingsystems/team/faculty/moebius/">Dr Wolfram Moebius</a>): <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/studying/funding/award/?id=2959">link</a>.</li>
<li style="margin-left: 40px;"> Acoustic imaging in turbid environments (in collaboration with <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/physics-astronomy/staff/JRSamble">Prof. J. Roy Sambles</a>): <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/studying/funding/award/?id=2845">link</a> (info available soon).</li>
</ul>    
And
<ul>
<li style="margin-left: 40px;">Towards flexible micro-endoscopy: compressive characterisation and control of light propagation through multi-mode optical fibres (first supervisor <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/physics-astronomy/staff/dp413">Dr Dave Phillips</a>): <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/studying/funding/award/?id=2939">link</a>.</li>
<li style="margin-left: 40px;">All dielectric phase-change metamaterial-based holography (first supervisor <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/engineering/staff/dwright0">Prof C. David Wright</a>): <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/studying/funding/award/?id=2839">link</a>.</li>
</ul>      
