          <span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span
                style="font-weight: bold;">17 July 2014</span><br />
            </span></span>New paper published!<br />
          The paper is entitled <span style="font-style: italic;">"Superpixel-based
            spatial amplitude and phase modulation using a digital micromirror
            device"</span>, and describes a novel method to achieve complete
          amplitude and phase modulation. A lot of credit goes to S.A Goorden,
          who had the original idea and did a large chunk of the work. You can
          find the paper <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/oe/abstract.cfm?uri=oe-22-15-17999">here</a>,
          or you can download the pdf directly from <a href="papers/OptExpress2014.pdf">here</a>.<br />
