          <span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span
                style="font-weight: bold;">06 August 2013</span><br />
            </span></span>Starting next September I will begin a new appointment
          as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lecturer#Academic_usage">Lecturer</a>
          (the British way of calling an Assistant Professor) at the <a href="http://www.exeter.ac.uk/">University
            of Exeter</a>. In particular I will be part of the <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/physics-astronomy/research/emag/">Electromagnetic
            and Acoustic Materials group</a> in the <a href="http://emps.exeter.ac.uk/physics-astronomy/">Physics
            and Astronomy Department</a>. I will start my own lab, working on
          light scattering in disordered media and imaging in turbid materials.<br />
          This is a new beginning and, as such, it is very exciting and a bit
          scary. Finger crossed!<br />
          <br />
